<item>
            <title>[HIVE-9474] truncate table changes permissions on the target</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-9474</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Create a table test(a string); &lt;br/&gt;
Hive&amp;gt; create table test(key string);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change the /user/hive/warehouse/test  permission to something else other than the default, like 777.&lt;br/&gt;
Hive&amp;gt; dfs -chmod 777 /user/hive/warehouse/test;&lt;br/&gt;
Hive&amp;gt; dfs -ls -d /user/hive/warehouse/test;&lt;br/&gt;
drwxrwxrwx   - axu wheel         68 2015-01-26 18:45 /user/hive/warehouse/test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then truncate table test; &lt;br/&gt;
Hive&amp;gt; truncate table test;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The permission goes back to the default.&lt;br/&gt;
hive&amp;gt; dfs -ls -d /user/hive/warehouse/test;&lt;br/&gt;
drwxr-xr-x   - axu wheel         68 2015-01-27 10:09 /user/hive/warehouse/test&lt;/p&gt;</description>
