                            <comment id="14293632" author="aihuaxu" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 14:58:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brocknoland&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brocknoland&quot;&gt;brocknoland&lt;/a&gt; Can you help review the change? Should be trivial. The failed test case was not due  to the change. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14293663" author="aihuaxu" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 15:11:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Truncate is implemented as deleting the folder and recreating the folder while the file permission is not carried over. The fix is to recreating the folder with the existing permission.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14293925" author="brocknoland" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 18:30:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Change looks great! Unfortunately the test doesn&apos;t do much because of path masking. You might consider a test similar to &lt;tt&gt;TestJDBCDriver2&lt;/tt&gt; but in a new class since that is getting bloated. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=szehon&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;szehon&quot;&gt;szehon&lt;/a&gt; also has a test somewhere which tests file persm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14293928" author="szehon" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 18:34:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I hit the same issue when trying to make a test for permission inheritance that does manual comparison of permission using HDFS api&apos;s.  You can put a new test in FolderPermissionTestBase, it will get executed by subclasses TestExtendedAcls and TestFolderPermissions.  Else, you can make a new test that is similar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14293930" author="aihuaxu" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 18:34:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Brock. Yeah, the path is masked. I will take a look at TestJDBCDriver2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14293934" author="aihuaxu" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 18:36:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great. I will follow your test case. Thanks. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=szehon&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;szehon&quot;&gt;szehon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14294085" author="szehon" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 19:56:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Aihua, this looks good but a thought occurred to me.  We would need to also make sure the HDFS extendedAcl&apos;s are preserved in case of permission inheritance (this is in additional to file permission).  So the code would look like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        HdfsFileStatus fullFileStatus = shim.getFullFileStatus(conf, fs, location);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
          shim.setFullFileStatus(conf, fullFileStatus, fs, location);
        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (Exception e) {
          LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Error setting permissions of &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + location, e);
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can check FileUtils as a reference.  I believe we won&apos;t need to add an additional test as by putting it in this base test, TestExtendedAcls will also test this as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14294347" author="aihuaxu" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 22:48:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch updated to use fileStatus approach to consider the ACL permission. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14294352" author="szehon" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 22:49:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Aihua!  Just one more small thing, can we catch the exception and log it?  Some file system doesnt support extended Acl&apos;s, we only want to make the best effort.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14294444" author="aihuaxu" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 23:59:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got it. Thanks, Szehon. Just updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
